The global problem of cardiovascular disease.

Yusuf S(1).

Author information:
(1)McMaster University, Hamilton, Ontario.

The greatest cause of death throughout the world today is noncommunicable 
disease. In Western societies, coronary artery disease is a principal cause of 
death. In developing countries, the incidence of coronary disease is rising as 
well. Heart disease often occurs in younger persons in developing societies, 
resulting in a disproportionately greater number of years of life lost. The 
reason for this change in global patterns of mortality is that deaths from 
infectious diseases are declining, resulting in greater life expectancy and 
changing lifestyles.

